President Obama called French President Hollande to offer his condolences and express solidarity after the terrorist attack in Paris. He reiterated that Americans stand with the people of France and offered the resources of the United States to help identify and bring to justice the perpetrators. President Hollande thanked Obama for his support and provided an update on the steps being taken to care for the victims and arrest those responsible. He affirmed that France will continue to defend the values of freedom and tolerance.